title: Guide
text: accurately visualize average wine point rankings country, use map_data dataset create world map average wine points country.  map shows European countries produce wines favored, Canada, India, China Australia good average points wines.
code: wine %>%    filter(!is.na(country)) %>%   group_by(country) %>%   summarise(mean = mean(points, na.rm = TRUE),             total_wine = n()) %>%   right_join(map_data("world"),              by = c("country" = "region")) %>%   ggplot(mapping = aes(x = long,                        y = lat,                        group = group)) +   geom_polygon(aes(fill = mean)) +   scale_fill_continuous(low = "#9DBF9E",                         high = "darkred",                         na.value = "snow2") +   coord_map(xlim = c(-180, 180),             ylim = c(-60, 80)) +   theme(axis.title.x = element_blank(),         axis.text.x = element_blank(),         axis.ticks.x = element_blank(),         axis.title.y = element_blank(),         axis.text.y = element_blank(),         axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),         panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white"))
